display

public java.lang.String display()
Changes a GnDataObject value for a supported key of display value. If the value does not exist, it will be added. If the value does exist, it will be changed. If NULL or an empty string is passed in, the value will be deleted.

Parameters:
value - set Value corresponding to the specified GnDataObject value key

Remarks:

Use this function to edit an existing value of display value. Note that the value must already exist on the editable GnDataObject.
